1.en: Mr. ZHU: (Through Translator) One hundred years ago, he was the supreme ruler, and ordinary people weren't even allowed to look at him.
1.cn: 朱诚如：100年前，光绪皇帝是最高无上的统治者，平民甚至都不被允许见他。

2.en: Harry's appeal stems from his role as a very ordinary boy who finds himself in extraordinary situations.
2.cn: 哈利的魅力来自于他的角色，一个发现自己身处不寻常境遇中的平凡男孩。

3.en: As the central bank has tightened monetary policy, this has made it harder for the bank to win the business of ordinary savers.
3.cn: 随着中国央行收紧货币政策，该行赢得普通储户的难度增大了。

0.en: I know I'm not an ordinary 10-year-old kid. I mean, I do ordinary things.
0.cn: 我知道自己不是普通的10岁小孩。其实，我做的事都很普通。

1.en: Maybe the truth is, I'm really not so ordinary. Maybe if we knew what other people were thinking we'd know that no one's ordinary.
1.cn: 也许事实就是，我没有那么的普通。如果你能看透每一个人的心，就会知道没有人是普通的。

2.en: Perhaps the identification was a mistake. Is he very distinctive to look at? Not very. Quite ordinary, in fact.
2.cn: 或许是看错了呢，他长得很特别吗？也不算，挺普通的。

3.en: Little snarky there, cello Lessons. And we have this completely ordinary cylinder. If you'd like to examine it...
3.cn: 吐槽过分了吧，学大提琴的。这里还有一个十分普通的圆筒，你们也可以检查一下。

4.en: This is an ordinary top hat. You've chosen that card freely. I do not have a set of lock picks lodged in my keister.
4.cn: 这是一顶普通的礼帽哦，这张牌是你随便抽的哦，我的屁眼里可没夹着开锁工具哦。

5.en: The depth of Eurus's psychosis and the extent of her abilities couldn't hope to be contained in any ordinary institution.
5.cn: 欧罗斯严重的精神疾病和她高超的能力，让她不可能待在普通的病院里。

6.en: These principles took me from being a very ordinary middle class kid from Long Island to becoming very successful as judged by conventional measures.
6.cn: 这些法则让我从一个普通的长岛来的中学小孩变成传统意义上非常成功的人。

7.en: But none of them have made me look ordinary.
7.cn: 但我还是没法变成普通人那样。

8.en: Thank you. No, thank you. And thank you, ordinary person.
8.cn: 谢谢。不，谢谢你，还有谢谢你，普通人。

9.en: Ordinary, yet I sense it is dripping with magical potential.
9.cn: 看似普通，不过我感觉到它隐隐散发的魔力了。

10.en: I just don't look ordinary when I'm doing these things. Not even my birth was ordinary.
10.cn: 只是我做事的样子和普通小孩不一样。我出生时的情况也跟他们不一样。

11.en: I know I'll never just be an ordinary kid. Ordinary kids don't make other kids run away from playgrounds.
11.cn: 我知道自己永远不会像普通孩子那样。普通孩子不会把其他孩子从游乐园吓跑。

12.en: This is great. Look at me. I'm in the real world of ordinary people just living their ordinary, colorless workaday lives.
12.cn: 真不错，看看我我生活在普通人的平凡世界中，过着他们无趣平常的一天。

13.en: So your dad dies, you can saddle for less than an ordinary life.
13.cn: 就因为你父亲死了，你连日子都不想过了。

14.en: Oh, that's ordinary in hot countries. It won't mean any disrespect.
14.cn: 这在热带国家很常见，不代表不敬。

15.en: No. No. I'm completely ordinary. That's right she is in the best way.
15.cn: 不 我很正常。没错她就是，以最好的方式。

16.en: Okay, I'm at work, ordinary day, you know, chop chop chop, saute, saute, saute.
16.cn: 我在上班，跟平常的一天一样，切切切，煎煎煎。

17.en: It needs to decide is this person's behavior typical or is it out of the ordinary?
17.cn: 大脑需要决定这个人的行为合乎常理吗？还是违背常理？

18.en: Me? Voldemort tried to kill me? Yes. That ain't no ordinary cut on your forehead, Harry.
18.cn: 我？伏地魔想要杀我？是的，你额头上的疤可非同寻常，哈利。

19.en: We say that it has a gravitational pressure, which ordinary matter and dark matter do not.
19.cn: 暗能量具有一种重力压力，这是普通物质和暗物质所不具有的。
